The paper proposes a deep convolutional neural network for solving inverse problems in imaging, which is a topic related to computer vision (cs.CV). The proposed method involves using residual learning and multiresolution decomposition, which are techniques commonly used in deep learning (cs.LG). The paper also discusses the challenges of hyperparameter selection, which is a topic related to artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The proposed method involves iterative algorithms, which is a topic related to numerical analysis (cs.NA).
